in the atmosphere which the gods can sense more easily than their mortal counterparts can be felt about Olympus and her many wide-ranging halls built by lame Hephaistos. <br><br>Through the main hall where the gods meet together for feast and council, tall, barrel-chested Poseidon makes his way with barely a garment on, but his golden sandles strapped tightly around the muscle of his calf and the golden crown that nearly always adorns his head. Now as he heads on his way the chanting of Demeter reaches his ears. Poseidon looks about and finds the Goddess of the Harvest alone on the balcony looking to be in a sort of supplication. <br><br>Walking up behind her slowly and without a sound Poseidon looks into whats happening. Peering over the balcony the immortal's shadow falls over his sister's form and the breeze wavers his dark locks. In winged words he speaks to her.<br><br>&quot;I like the change sister. The best time of the year for me and many another. For you too, is it not the time to reunite with Persephone?&quot;<br><br> <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uxxdemeterxx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xxDemeterxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 42<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/10/02 1:34:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.picturesof.net/_pictures/flowers_calla_lilies_6age1_TN.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Another Weather Change</span><hr size=1> ::She smiled as she felt the presence of her brother. He had his sides that she would never like nor understand, but he was her brother and always held a sacred space in her heart. She watched the changes below and nodded at his words.::<br><br>&quot;Yes, she is due back soon. She can take her time, but let it be known, if she doesnt come back. I will persoanlly go and get her myself. I do not want to punish the earth, but I will, and Zeus does not wish that, ad it will be on her head.&quot;<br><br>::She turned and looked to him:::<br>&quot;How are things beneath the sea?&quot;<br> <p>:*: Goddess Demeter, Goddess of the Harvest. Controller of the seasons and weather. :*:</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(3/16/02 3:11:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Request</span><hr size=1> ::Hades sat upon his throne.  He sat very regally, almost seeming to be made of stone, his alabaster skin also contributed to this vision.  Once Persephone spoke, he turned his head to look at her.  Without saying a word, he stood up and walked beside her.  He held out his arm, and gently took her arm as he bowed slightly.  He began walking with her towards her private garden.  He had a feeling about what it is she wished to talk about, but he would never actually know until he asked her::<br><br>&quot;And what is it you wish to discuss, my Love?&quot;<br><br>::He turned to face her and look into her eyes.  His eyes gleamed with a tenderness that he showed only to her:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 288<br> <font co