iting for Hades, Persephone turns and leaves the hall quickly. Her snow white silk toga and white, long, cloak like veil sway and billow gracefully with her walk. The diamonds in her bracelets, necklace, wedding band, ad as well as the subtle ones in her pinned up curly hair twinkle and sparkle brilliantly in the bright yet dark sunlight of the morning. When she gets to the carriage, she takes the hand of the driver and gently steps inside. After she makes herself comfortable inside gold interior painted carriage on plush rosed colored velvet cushion, she leans her head out the window::<br><br>Do not leave just yet driver. My husband will be coming shortly to escort me to my mother. ::As she puts her head back in, the driver looks straight ahead and gulps hard at the thought of seeing the great lord Hades:<br><br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uixlordhadesxi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IX Lord Hades XI</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/1/02 4:34:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A solemn goodbye...</span><hr size=1> ::Hades slowly stood up as he did not eat much of his food, save a few bites.  He rarely ate, all the sustenance he ever needed was in a few bites.  He followed behind Persephone as she rose up.  He knew her feelings about leaving were despair.  He seemed to get into the carriage with no effort.  As a matter of fact, it seemed as though he didn't even use a door.  He sat beside his wife and took her hand::<br><br>&quot;I find it Ironic, you used to dread coming to Tartarus, now it seems as though you dread leaving.&quot;<br><br>::Hades seemed to have a knowing smirk on his face.::<br><br>&quot;Driver, go on.&quot;  ::He motioned for the carriage to begin::<br><br>::He then whispered in Persephone's ear:: &quot;You know I could just always take you up in my Chariot.  It would you be you and I alone.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/upersephoneqofu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 128<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/1/02 9:31:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.farbelow.com/yasmine-bleeth/25.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Tears</span><hr size=1> ::Persephone smiles a little on his comment about her not wanting to leave. It was somewhat true, she was always willing to leave to Tartarus and this time was no different from the other times. But it was leaving her beloved Hades that broke her heart in two. It was just last spring that she trully fell in love with him, and it was also just last spring that they had finlly comsumated their marriage. To her, six months without her dear Hades and her private flowers seemed like damned eternity::<br><br>::She then turned to him and nodded to his suggestion::. That would be a good idea, and the coach can continue on its way so my mother as planned me and her can ride the carriage to Olympus. ::she looks down and her face begins to quiver and her lips begin to tremble, which always means she's going to cry. Of course, tears shoot out from her eyes moments later and she lays herself in Hades arms crying hard on his chest:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Silver Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 294<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/9/02 7:52:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://web.uvic.ca/grs/bowman/myth/images/haifa/h89.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Waiting......</span><hr size=1> The great of the immortals entered the coach with Demeter and all the while kept to himself. His silence was as striking physical as that of a mute and his thoughts were far, far away from where he was at the moment. The ride was short and comfortable and they were quickly brought to a place where the god supposed Persephone was to be delivered in due time.<br><br>Stillness was spread throughout the field and nothing seemed alive really, but to be an illusion. Poseidon stood by Demeters side and felt alone as he watched the open portal leading into a realm that few have ben to and returned from be they god or man. Demeter was like an unreal depiction of some thought in his mind and he stared at her for a long time. The sharp and warped light and movement from the portal still clung to his attention and he returned his gaze to it awaiting Persephone.<br> <p>Poseidon~Lord of the Deep Blue Sea~Patron Of Horses And Sailors~</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugaiaofearth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gaia of Earth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(4/10/02 3:50:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=242.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> The Earth</span><hr size=1> The Great Earth Goddess watched Persophone, Hades, Demeter, and Poseidon in her